<h1 id="installation">Installation</h1>

<p>To install we will use the snap. Just remembering that the snap is available for several distributions, such as: Arch, Gentoo, Linux Mint and others. The cool thing about it is that we will avoid problems with Docker versions.</p>

<ul>
  <li><code class="highlighter-rouge">sudo snap install docker</code> - Installs Docker</li>
  <li><code class="highlighter-rouge">ps -A | grep docker</code> - Check if the daemon is already running</li>
  <li><code class="highlighter-rouge">sudo docker run hello-world</code> - Running your first container</li>
</ul>

<p>The output will be something like:</p>

